<div id="p52429" class="blockpost rowodd">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#3</span> <a href="viewtopic.php?pid=52429#p52429">2017-05-29 12:05:49</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postbody">
				<div class="postleft">
					<dl>
						<dt><strong>Head_on_a_Stick</strong></dt>
						<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
						<dd class="postavatar"><img src="https://forums.bunsenlabs.org/img/avatars/74.png?m=1494016729" width="60" height="60" alt="" /></dd>
						<dd><span>From: London</span></dd>
						<dd><span>Registered: 2015-09-29</span></dd>
						<dd><span>Posts: 8,759</span></dd>
						<dd class="usercontacts"><span class="website"><a href="https://www.kingraymotorcycles.co.uk/" rel="nofollow">Website</a></span></dd>
					</dl>
				</div>
				<div class="postright">
					<h3>Re: lightdm and .xinitrc</h3>
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p><a href="https://github.com/BunsenLabs/bunsen-configs/blob/master/skel/.config/openbox/autostart" rel="nofollow">~/.config/openbox/autostart</a> is used to start most of the desktop programs in BunsenLabs, this file is parsed whether LightDM is used or not as long as <em>openbox-session</em> is set as <em>x-session-manager</em> in <strong>/etc/alternatives</strong></p><p><a href="https://github.com/BunsenLabs/bunsen-configs/blob/master/skel/.xsessionrc" rel="nofollow">~/.xsessionrc</a> is used to set environmental variables and suchlike, that file is read by LightDM and most other display managers.</p><p>It is also possible to drop .desktop files in <strong>~/.config/autostart</strong> and LightDM will honour these as per the <a href="https://specifications.freedesktop.org/autostart-spec/0.5/ar01s02.html" rel="nofollow">freedesktop.org specification</a>.</p><p>If you want to use <strong>~/.xinitrc</strong> with LightDM then symlink that file to <strong>~/.xsession</strong> and select &quot;Default XSession&quot; as the desktop in LightDM.</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>ln -s ~/.xinitrc ~/.xsession</code></pre></div><p>Or, if you are as allergic to symlinks as I am:</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>echo &quot;. ~/.xinitrc&quot; &gt; ~/.xsession</code></pre></div><p>I&#039;ve just checked my Debian jessie system and that uses a slightly more robust version:</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code># ~/.xsession
/bin/bash --login -i ~/.xinitrc</code></pre></div>
					</div>
					<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr /><p><em>“Et ignotas animum dimittit in artes.”</em> — Ovid, Metamorphoses, VIII., 18.</p><p><a href="https://forums.bunsenlabs.org/misc.php?action=rules" rel="nofollow">Forum Rules</a>&#160; &#160;•&#160; &#160;<a href="http://www.co.kerr.tx.us/it/howtoreport.html" rel="nofollow">How to report a problem</a>&#160; &#160;•&#160; &#160;<a href="https://suckless.org/rocks" rel="nofollow">Software that rocks</a></p></div>
				</div>
