					</dl>
				</div>
				<div class="postright">
					<h3>Re: lightdm and .xinitrc</h3>
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p><strong>.xsessionrc</strong> will be read by a LightDm-free plain &#039;startx&#039; session too.</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>grep -r &#039;.xsessionrc&#039; /etc/X11</code></pre></div><p>Although it&#039;s <em>supposed</em> to be for evvars and the like, you can use any shell commands you want, just like .config/openbox/<strong>autostart</strong>, and .config/openbox/<strong>environment</strong> for that matter. The difference of course is that the openbox files won&#039;t be run by other window managers.</p><p><strong>.xinitrc</strong> will likely be ignored by lightdm (haven&#039;t tested) and with startx its presence in ~/ will cause all the usual Debian startup commands (see /etc/X11/Xsession.d/) to be skipped, so you have to do everything yourself. Some people might prefer that.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr /><p><em>...elevator in the Brain Hotel, broken down but just as well...</em><br />( a boring <a href="http://asazuke.com" rel="nofollow">Japan blog</a> (currently paused), idle <a href="https://twitter.com/john_raff" rel="nofollow">Twitterings</a> and <a href="https://github.com/johnraff" rel="nofollow">GitStuff</a> )</p><p><a href="https://forums.bunsenlabs.org/viewtopic.php?id=6461" rel="nofollow">Introduction to the Bunsenlabs Lithium Desktop</a></p></div>
				</div>
