					<h3>Re: lightdm and .xinitrc</h3>
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p>.xinitrc is not needed in the standard Debian boot-up. My understanding is that if it does exist, then a lot of - going on most of - those other files are ignored. </p><p>It dates from 2012, but back in #! I dived into this stuff because it was bothering me, and wrote it up. Now reposted here: <a href="https://forums.bunsenlabs.org/viewtopic.php?id=3774" rel="nofollow">https://forums.bunsenlabs.org/viewtopic.php?id=3774</a> If you&#039;re interested...</p>
