				<div class="postright">
					<h3>Re: lightdm and .xinitrc</h3>
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p>I think if ~/.xinitrc is used then Debian assumes that the user wants to specify *exactly* what starts in that file and nowhere else.</p><p>Thanks for re-posting that guide johnraff, I keep forgetting about the /etc/X11/Xsession.d quirk&#160; <img src="https://forums.bunsenlabs.org/plugins/ezbbc/style/smilies/ops.png" alt="ops" /></p><p>EDIT:</p><div class="quotebox"><cite>BLizgreat! wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>No mention of .xinitrc there, though assume some display-managers could check for one and execute if found.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>No, display managers will ignore ~/.xinitrc</p>
						<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by Head_on_a_Stick (2017-06-02 07:09:25)</em></p>
